								Attention LMCHS students and parents/guardians:  Update Friday, March 27, 2020
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_3_title"><p>
								Today Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham announced school closings must continue to prevent potential spread of COVID-19.  All schools in NM including LMCHS will shift to a learn-at-home model as we will remain closed for the rest of the academic year.  We have developed technology-based and non-technology based continuous learning plans.  Administrative staff will be calling all students beginning Monday, March 30 to provide general information and updates, answer any questions, and communicate the plan for our learn-at-home program.  Please see the attached press release from the NMPED and we look forward to speaking with you soon.  Take care and stay safe and healthy. - Mr. Martinez
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_4" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_4_title">
